<b>About Songs and Melee - </b>12/12/03 7:52:19 PM<br>~ <b>Katter</b><blockquote>Lynae to answer your questions.<br><br>You can melee and have an instrument in your hands at the same time.  However most instruments in the game are two handed particularly the vendor bought ones and therefore you cannot wield a weapon while having it equiped which is usually in the secondary slot.  Think about it most instruments are two handed when played and you usually hold the instrument with your left hand.  You can melee however using hand to hand.  We aren't great at it but it is better than nothing if you are in close with the mob.<br><br>Now there are several instruments that are one handed, there are usually costly to get or come from a quest.  These are usually in the primary hand and you can weild a weapon in your secondary.  The point is we do so much damage with our songs that having a weapon in our primary is overpowering.<br><br>In fact, and correct me if I am wrong but the only instruments that can be wielded in the secondary and allow you to use a weapon in the primary are the instuments that are also weapons, several drop in Luclin and of course the epic.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
